peopleAlsoAsk.question: What years were Duraglas bottles?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet:
The term Duraglas was first used by the Owens-Illinois Glass Company in 1940, with stippling on the bottom of the jugs, and the cursive embossed signature remained in use until 1964. Clear glass jug, ca. 1950s, good condition, resale value $12-$15.
